<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">Corporate Investment Banking</h1>

<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>

<p class="bac">Senior coverage bankers in Corporate and Investment Banking (CIB) are at the forefront of every client relationship. CIB client managers take the time to understand what drives each client – their immediate objectives, long-term goals and ever-changing competitive environments. As a member of the Bank of America CIB team, you will:</p>
<ul class="bac">
<li>Lead client relationship teams for high-profile clients.</li>
<li>Help create opportunities for clients by drawing upon the bank&acute;s broad expertise and resources.</li>
<li>Partner with product and industry specialists to seamlessly deliver insightful solutions.</li>
<li>Support U.S. clients operating outside of the United States.</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">In Asia, our Corporate and Investment Banking (CIB) group targets opportunities where our global product platform and international expertise give us a competitive advantage. We are achieving this by investing in integrated origination teams that leverage our superior client relationships as well as the bank&acute;s U.S. and European strengths, financing capabilities and capital resources.</p>

<p class="bac">CIB in Asia is organized along geographic lines with regional industry and segment support from local locations across Asia.  Senior relationship bankers are dedicated to gaining in-depth understanding of our clients&acute; business issues to build strong, partnership-based relationships and deliver solution-orientated dialogue and ideas to our valued clients.  Coverage bankers with a team of corporate finance associates partner with product and risk teams throughout the bank to deliver holistic, integrated financial solutions to our clients.  The Asia client portfolio is characterized by strong, longstanding relationships with leading companies in Asia and across the globe.</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview</h2>

<p class="bac">As active team members in the Corporate and Investment Banking group, Associates help orchestrate integrated financial solutions and strategic advisory transactions, through</p>
<ul class="bac">
<li>Developing and maintaining financial models </li>
<li>Supporting various financial analyses, including valuations and merger consequences </li>
<li>Conducting comprehensive and in–depth company and industry research </li>
<li>Preparing presentation and other client materials </li>
<li>Participating in due diligence sessions </li>
<li>Communicating and interacting with team members and other colleagues across the company</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications</h2>

<p class="bac">Candidates must have obtained or are realistically expecting to obtain an MBA degree from a premier business school.  Candidate should have deep and broad finance knowledge, excellent verbal and written communication skills, and strong personal leadership skills.  </p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training</h2>
<p class="bac">As an Associate, you will begin your career at Bank of America with an extensive training program in New York. The first part of the program combines Associates from all lines of business.  The full program is a combination of classroom instruction, e-learning modules, case studies and presentations. Throughout the program, you&acute;ll have ample opportunities to work closely with professionals and peers throughout our organization. This is a great opportunity to build a network of colleagues from across the company that will prove to be a tremendous resource to you throughout your career.</p>
<p class="bac">After completing the program in New York, your learning journey will continue and you will go through a practical training process in Asia which will allow you to hone the skills you need for a successful career at the bank.</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Placement</h2>

<p class="bac">Associates work in Mumbai or New Delhi, India. Offers are made for a specific product desk, based on candidate preference and business need.  Throughout the recruiting and orientation process, candidates have the opportunities to learn about various desks and meet team members and colleagues from across the company.</p>


<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">


